text: It's mid-July at about 10:00 a.m., and I've just crashed in the Atacama Desert in South America
I'm 50 miles from a mining camp, the closest known settlement

The weather forecast calls for temperatures to reach 110 degrees today, which means the ground temperature will reach 130 degrees. You wear light clothing - a short-sleeved shirt, pants, socks and loafers.

My group has successfully rescued 15 of the items listed on the "Saved Items" page. Your task is to rank these items in order of their importance to your survival, from "1" being the most important item to "15" being the least important item.
You need to think about sorting
